label("$y$", (B + D)/2, S);
label("$z$", (C + D)/2, S);
label("$z$", (C + E)/2, NE);
[/asy]

Then $x + y = AB = 13$, $x + z = AC = 15$, and $y + z = BC = 14$.  Adding all these equations, we get $2x + 2y + 2z = 42$, so $x + y + z = 21$.  Subtracting the equation $x + z = 15$, we get $y = 6$.

